16.1
  1) Have you ever been to Paris? No, never.
  2) Have you ever played golf? Yes, many times.
  3) Have you ever been to Australia? No, never.
  4) Have you ever lost your passport? Yes, once.
  5) Have you ever slept in a park? No, never.
  6) Have you ever eaten Chinese food? Yes, a few times.
  7) Have you ever been to New York? Yes, twice.
  8) Have you ever broken your leg? Yes, once.
  
16.2
  1) Ann has never been to Paris.
  2) Ann has played golf many times.
  3) She hasn't been to Australia.
  4) She has lost her password.
  5) She has never slept in a park.
  6) She has eaten Chinese food a few times.
  7) Ann has been to New York twice.
  8) Ann has broken her leg once.
  9) I've never been to Paris.
  10) I've never been played golf.
  11) I've never been to Australia.
  12) I've never lost my password.
  13) I've never slept in a park at all.
  14) I've never eaten Chinese food at all.
  15) I've never been to New York.
  16) I've never broken my leg.
  
  16.3
    1) She has done many different jobs.
    2) She has travelled to many places.
    3) She has done a lot of interesting things.
    4) She has writen ten books.
    5) she has meeten a lot of interesting people.
    6) She has benn married five times.
    
  16.4
    1) He's on holiday at the moment. He's gone to Spain.
    2) Where is Jill? She's not here. I think she's gone to the bank.
    3) Hello, Pat. Where have you been. I'be gone to the bank.
    4) Have you been to Mexice? No, never.
    5) My parents aren't at home this evening. They've gone out.
    6) There's a new restaurant in town. Have you been to it? 
    7) Paris is a wonderful city. I'be been there many times.
    8) Helen was here earlier but I think she's gone now.
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  
